<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 5:46PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Wheeler
County through 615 PM CDT...
At 546 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Sweetwater, or 20 miles northeast of Shamrock, moving
southwest at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Wheeler and Twitty.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
